  "text": "Opiate-mediated renal function might be related to cardiovascular activities as well. Rats bred to be possess renal hypertension appear to have increased sensitivity to opiates, and this response might occur through an interaction with angiotensin II in the brain [CITATION_1] . In addition, kidney damage due to reperfusion after hemorrhage was inhibited by naloxone (11), suggesting that the endogenous opiates might be responsible for the tissue damage in that situation.",
